Field.Name: Thecodeindexfieldstartsat
Field.PromptText:
The code index field starts at zero(0) and is incremented up to seven(7) then reset to zero(0).
The codes range from one(1) to three(3) with correlating values of "One" to "Three".
Note that when a value is assigned to the codes field that is not defined in the codes table the codes field and its target field should be cleared.

Field.Name: Notes
Field.PromptText:
Notes:
You should be able to create a drop down without defining its source table. You may want to create the a set of drop down fields then go back and create their source tables and link them.
You should be able to select 'Use Existing' and then add another column to the table if needed.

Field.Name: Notes1
Field.PromptText:
Lateral selection happen when a value is selected via check code or another code field that changes the values available in the linked field.
In this example, a user can filter down to a list of cities by selecting [State] > [County] or selecting an airport code or hitting a command button that assigns the city.

Item.DescriptionLabel: Helium ( /ˈhiːliəm/ HEE-lee-əm) is a chemical element with symbol He and atomic number 2. It is a colorless, odorless, tasteless, non-toxic, inert, monatomic gas that heads the noble gas group in the periodic table.
Neon ( /ˈniːɒn/ NEE-on) is a chemical element with symbol Ne and atomic number 10. Although neon is a very common element in the universe, it is rare on Earth.
